Package src.ai.data.csv

Class CSVFile

java.lang.Object
src.ai.data.csv.CSVFile
public class CSVFile extends Object
A class to represent a CSV file with data, this class is responsible for both reading and storing the data that was found in the specified CSV file.
Author:
devinlinux

    • CSVFile

      protected CSVFile(String path, char separator, boolean containsHeader, List<String> ignoredColumns, Map<String,Class<?>> columnMap)
      Constructor to make a new CSVFile.
      Parameters:
      path - the path to the CSV file to read.
      separator - the separator that is being used in the CSV file. default is comma.
      containsHeader - whether the CSV file contains a header. default is true.
      ignoredColumns - the columns to ignore in the creation of the data frame. default is an empty List.
      columnMap - the Map of the names and data types of each column in the CSV file. default is an empty Map.
